{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011bzvcniF2PpC87c6QwNHn8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the key details:\n- Source: Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster (3 nodes: elasticsearch-0, 1, 2) - HTTPS with TLS, password \"elasticpass\"\n- Monitoring: Elasticsearch 7.17.9 (single-node, no auth, no TLS)\n\nI need to add Metricbeat and Filebeat sidecars to each Elasticsearch pod to ship monitoring data to the monitoring cluster.\n\nKey considerations:\n1. Metricbeat will collect metrics from Elasticsearch and ship to monitoring cluster\n2. Filebeat will collect logs from Elasticsearch and ship to monitoring cluster\n3. The source cluster uses HTTPS with TLS and authentication, while the monitoring cluster is plain HTTP with no auth\n4. I need to use Metricbeat 8.x to properly collect from the ES 8.11.1 source, and it can output to the 7.17.9 monitoring cluster without compatibility issues\n\nThe key insight is that Metricbeat version should match the source being monitored, so 8.x for ES 8.11.1, and the monitoring indices it creates will be in the 8.x format. The 7.17.9 monitoring cluster can receive these cross-version monitoring indices since it's at least 7.x.\n\nNow I'm planning the actual configuration: a Metricbeat sidecar running 8.11.1 that connects to the source ES instance locally and sends monitoring data to the monitoring cluster, plus a Filebeat sidecar for log collection.\n\nI need to create ConfigMaps for both beat configurations and then patch the StatefulSet to inject these sidecars. Let me first check the current elasticsearch.yml to see what I'm working with.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":801,"cache_read_input_tokens":34445,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":801},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_