{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WrMoaQx7FhupHuqhYDXUSb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Metricbeat is working on all 3 pods with successes. \n\nFilebeat has JSON parsing errors because the GC log files are not JSON format - they're plain text. I need to fix the Filebeat configuration to not try to parse non-JSON files as JSON.\n\nThe issue is the filebeat config has `parsers: [ndjson: ...]` applied to ALL paths including the GC log. I need to fix this.\n\nLet me update the filebeat config:\n1. Remove the JSON parser from the GC log path, or \n2. Use separate inputs for JSON logs and non-JSON logs\nI'm realizing the better approach is to split this into two separate inputs - one for JSON logs with the ndjson parser enabled, and another for the GC logs and other non-JSON formats without any parsing. The current config is matching both `*.json` and `*.log` files in the same input with JSON parsing applied to everything, which is causing the errors on the plain text logs.\n\nLet me also verify whether Filebeat is actually sending data despite these parse errors, since raw events should still get forwarded even when parsing fails. I need to check if there's a Filebeat index in the monitoring cluster and what documents are actually being indexed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3019,"cache_read_input_tokens":60241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3019},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c254387-153b-4876-b104-fac31aa7be5d","uuid":"8dd59c33-a360-4ad5-bd24-01e427610f7e","request_id":"req_011CcPHPuSgMYW4mxWLmUcHE"}
